{
  "texts": [
    "In addition to serving as the ISAC-BS, the UAV can also be the airborne user or target, which is an interesting scenario worth further investigation.",
    "AI-enabled near-field ISACThe future ISAC network will have extremely large-scale antenna arrays operating at higher (e.g., millimeter and sub Terahertz) carrier frequencies to meet the increasing communication and sensing requirements, resulting in a shift in propagation characteristics from far-field to near-field [247].",
    "Unlike the far-field, the near-field wireless channels are modeled as spherical wavefronts instead of planar wavefronts, which is expected to improve the performance of ISAC networks.",
    "On the one hand, the near-field beamforming can focus the beam energy on specific positions, thus improving the QoS at the desired users and mitigating the interference to the undesired users.",
    "On the other hand, the spherical wave propagation carries both angle and distance information, enabling high-resolution sensing and positioning."
  ]
}